{
  "text": "Non-denaturing polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis (PAGE) of the purified Lacps1 revealed a single laccase activity band (Figure 2a ), coincident with a single band after Coomassie Blue staining (Figure 2b ), confirming the homogeneity of the preparation. A single protein band corresponding to 65 kDa was also revealed after sodium dodecyl sulfate-PAGE (SDS-PAGE) analysis (Figure 2c ). The apparent molecular mass of Lacps1 estimated by gel filtration was 67 kDa, in good agreement with that estimated by SDS-PAGE, suggesting that the native enzyme was a monomer. Similar apparent molecular masses were reported for several laccases from other P. sanguineus strains [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] and other Pycnoporus species [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] .",
